8229#ifdef CONFIG_NET_POLL_CONTROLLER
8230/* Polling 'interrupt' - used by things like netconsole to send skbs
8231 * without having to re-enable interrupts. It's not called while
8232 * the interrupt routine is executing.
8233 */
8234static void igb_netpoll(struct net_device *netdev)
8235{
8236 struct igb_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
8237 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
8238 struct igb_q_vector *q_vector;
8239 int i;
8240
8241 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_q_vectors; i++) {
8242 q_vector = adapter->q_vector[i];
8243 if (adapter->flags & IGB_FLAG_HAS_MSIX)
8244 wr32(E1000_EIMC, q_vector->eims_value);
8245 else
8246 igb_irq_disable(adapter);
8247 napi_schedule(&q_vector->napi);
8248 }
8249}
8250#endif /* CONFIG_NET_POLL_CONTROLLER */
8251
8252/**
8253 * igb_io_error_detected - called when PCI error is detected
8254 * @pdev: Pointer to PCI device
8255 * @state: The current pci connection state
8256 *
8257 * This function is called after a PCI bus error affecting
8258 * this device has been detected.
8259 **/
8260static pci_ers_result_t igb_io_error_detected(struct pci_dev *pdev,
8261 pci_channel_state_t state)
8262{
8263 struct net_device *netdev = pci_get_drvdata(pdev);
8264 struct igb_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
8265
8266 netif_device_detach(netdev);
8267
8268 if (state == pci_channel_io_perm_failure)
8269 return PCI_ERS_RESULT_DISCONNECT;
8270
8271 if (netif_running(netdev))
8272 igb_down(adapter);
8273 pci_disable_device(pdev);
8274
8275 /* Request a slot slot reset. */
8276 return PCI_ERS_RESULT_NEED_RESET;
8277}
8278
8279/**
8280 * igb_io_slot_reset - called after the pci bus has been reset.
8281 * @pdev: Pointer to PCI device
8282 *
8283 * Restart the card from scratch, as if from a cold-boot. Implementation
8284 * resembles the first-half of the igb_resume routine.
8285 **/
8286static pci_ers_result_t igb_io_slot_reset(struct pci_dev *pdev)
8287{
8288 struct net_device *netdev = pci_get_drvdata(pdev);
8289 struct igb_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
8290 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
8291 pci_ers_result_t result;
8292 int err;
8293
8294 if (pci_enable_device_mem(pdev)) {
8295 dev_err(&pdev->dev,
8296 "Cannot re-enable PCI device after reset.\n");
8297 result = PCI_ERS_RESULT_DISCONNECT;
8298 } else {
8299 pci_set_master(pdev);
8300 pci_restore_state(pdev);
8301 pci_save_state(pdev);
8302
8303 pci_enable_wake(pdev, PCI_D3hot, 0);
8304 pci_enable_wake(pdev, PCI_D3cold, 0);
8305
8306 /* In case of PCI error, adapter lose its HW address
8307 * so we should re-assign it here.
8308 */
8309 hw->hw_addr = adapter->io_addr;
8310
8311 igb_reset(adapter);
8312 wr32(E1000_WUS, ~0);
8313 result = PCI_ERS_RESULT_RECOVERED;
8314 }
8315
8316 err = pci_cleanup_aer_uncorrect_error_status(pdev);
8317 if (err) {
8318 dev_err(&pdev->dev,
8319 "pci_cleanup_aer_uncorrect_error_status failed 0x%0x\n",
8320 err);
8321 /* non-fatal, continue */
8322 }
8323
8324 return result;
8325}
8326
8327/**
8328 * igb_io_resume - called when traffic can start flowing again.
8329 * @pdev: Pointer to PCI device
8330 *
8331 * This callback is called when the error recovery driver tells us that
8332 * its OK to resume normal operation. Implementation resembles the
8333 * second-half of the igb_resume routine.
8334 */
8335static void igb_io_resume(struct pci_dev *pdev)
8336{
8337 struct net_device *netdev = pci_get_drvdata(pdev);
8338 struct igb_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
8339
8340 if (netif_running(netdev)) {
8341 if (igb_up(adapter)) {
8342 dev_err(&pdev->dev, "igb_up failed after reset\n");
8343 return;
8344 }
8345 }
8346
8347 netif_device_attach(netdev);
8348
8349 /* let the f/w know that the h/w is now under the control of the
8350 * driver.
8351 */
8352 igb_get_hw_control(adapter);
8353}
8354
8355/**
8356 * igb_rar_set_index - Sync RAL[index] and RAH[index] registers with MAC table
8357 * @adapter: Pointer to adapter structure
8358 * @index: Index of the RAR entry which need to be synced with MAC table
8359 **/
8360static void igb_rar_set_index(struct igb_adapter *adapter, u32 index)
8361{
8362 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
8363 u32 rar_low, rar_high;
8364 u8 *addr = adapter->mac_table[index].addr;
8365
8366 /* HW expects these to be in network order when they are plugged
8367 * into the registers which are little endian. In order to guarantee
8368 * that ordering we need to do an leXX_to_cpup here in order to be
8369 * ready for the byteswap that occurs with writel
8370 */
8371 rar_low = le32_to_cpup((__le32 *)(addr));
8372 rar_high = le16_to_cpup((__le16 *)(addr + 4));
8373
8374 /* Indicate to hardware the Address is Valid. */
8375 if (adapter->mac_table[index].state & IGB_MAC_STATE_IN_USE) {
8376 if (is_valid_ether_addr(addr))
8377 rar_high |= E1000_RAH_AV;
8378
8379 if (hw->mac.type == e1000_82575)
8380 rar_high |= E1000_RAH_POOL_1 *
8381 adapter->mac_table[index].queue;
8382 else
8383 rar_high |= E1000_RAH_POOL_1 <<
8384 adapter->mac_table[index].queue;
8385 }
8386
8387 wr32(E1000_RAL(index), rar_low);
8388 wrfl();
8389 wr32(E1000_RAH(index), rar_high);
8390 wrfl();
8391}
8392
8393static int igb_set_vf_mac(struct igb_adapter *adapter,
8394 int vf, unsigned char *mac_addr)
8395{
8396 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
8397 /* VF MAC addresses start at end of receive addresses and moves
8398 * towards the first, as a result a collision should not be possible
8399 */
8400 int rar_entry = hw->mac.rar_entry_count - (vf + 1);
8401 unsigned char *vf_mac_addr = adapter->vf_data[vf].vf_mac_addresses;
8402
8403 ether_addr_copy(vf_mac_addr, mac_addr);
8404 ether_addr_copy(adapter->mac_table[rar_entry].addr, mac_addr);
8405 adapter->mac_table[rar_entry].queue = vf;
8406 adapter->mac_table[rar_entry].state |= IGB_MAC_STATE_IN_USE;
8407 igb_rar_set_index(adapter, rar_entry);
8408
8409 return 0;
8410}
8411
8412static int igb_ndo_set_vf_mac(struct net_device *netdev, int vf, u8 *mac)
8413{
8414 struct igb_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
8415
8416 if (vf >= adapter->vfs_allocated_count)
8417 return -EINVAL;
8418
8419 /* Setting the VF MAC to 0 reverts the IGB_VF_FLAG_PF_SET_MAC
8420 * flag and allows to overwrite the MAC via VF netdev. This
8421 * is necessary to allow libvirt a way to restore the original
8422 * MAC after unbinding vfio-pci and reloading igbvf after shutting
8423 * down a VM.
8424 */
8425 if (is_zero_ether_addr(mac)) {
8426 adapter->vf_data[vf].flags &= ~IGB_VF_FLAG_PF_SET_MAC;
8427 dev_info(&adapter->pdev->dev,
8428 "remove administratively set MAC on VF %d\n",
8429 vf);
8430 } else if (is_valid_ether_addr(mac)) {
8431 adapter->vf_data[vf].flags |= IGB_VF_FLAG_PF_SET_MAC;
8432 dev_info(&adapter->pdev->dev, "setting MAC %pM on VF %d\n",
8433 mac, vf);
8434 dev_info(&adapter->pdev->dev,
8435 "Reload the VF driver to make this change effective.");
8436 /* Generate additional warning if PF is down */
8437 if (test_bit(__IGB_DOWN, &adapter->state)) {
8438 dev_warn(&adapter->pdev->dev,
8439 "The VF MAC address has been set, but the PF device is not up.\n");
8440 dev_warn(&adapter->pdev->dev,
8441 "Bring the PF device up before attempting to use the VF device.\n");
8442 }
8443 } else {
8444 return -EINVAL;
8445 }
8446 return igb_set_vf_mac(adapter, vf, mac);
8447}
8448
8449static int igb_link_mbps(int internal_link_speed)
8450{
8451 switch (internal_link_speed) {
8452 case SPEED_100:
8453 return 100;
8454 case SPEED_1000:
8455 return 1000;
8456 default:
8457 return 0;
8458 }
8459}
8460
8461static void igb_set_vf_rate_limit(struct e1000_hw *hw, int vf, int tx_rate,
8462 int link_speed)
8463{
8464 int rf_dec, rf_int;
8465 u32 bcnrc_val;
8466
8467 if (tx_rate != 0) {
8468 /* Calculate the rate factor values to set */
8469 rf_int = link_speed / tx_rate;
8470 rf_dec = (link_speed - (rf_int * tx_rate));
8471 rf_dec = (rf_dec * BIT(E1000_RTTBCNRC_RF_INT_SHIFT)) /
8472 tx_rate;
8473
8474 bcnrc_val = E1000_RTTBCNRC_RS_ENA;
8475 bcnrc_val |= ((rf_int << E1000_RTTBCNRC_RF_INT_SHIFT) &
8476 E1000_RTTBCNRC_RF_INT_MASK);
8477 bcnrc_val |= (rf_dec & E1000_RTTBCNRC_RF_DEC_MASK);
8478 } else {
8479 bcnrc_val = 0;
8480 }
8481
8482 wr32(E1000_RTTDQSEL, vf); /* vf X uses queue X */
8483 /* Set global transmit compensation time to the MMW_SIZE in RTTBCNRM
8484 * register. MMW_SIZE=0x014 if 9728-byte jumbo is supported.
8485 */
8486 wr32(E1000_RTTBCNRM, 0x14);
8487 wr32(E1000_RTTBCNRC, bcnrc_val);
8488}
8489
8490static void igb_check_vf_rate_limit(struct igb_adapter *adapter)
8491{
8492 int actual_link_speed, i;
8493 bool reset_rate = false;
8494
8495 /* VF TX rate limit was not set or not supported */
8496 if ((adapter->vf_rate_link_speed == 0) ||
8497 (adapter->hw.mac.type != e1000_82576))
8498 return;
8499
8500 actual_link_speed = igb_link_mbps(adapter->link_speed);
8501 if (actual_link_speed != adapter->vf_rate_link_speed) {
8502 reset_rate = true;
8503 adapter->vf_rate_link_speed = 0;
8504 dev_info(&adapter->pdev->dev,
8505 "Link speed has been changed. VF Transmit rate is disabled\n");
8506 }
8507
8508 for (i = 0; i < adapter->vfs_allocated_count; i++) {
8509 if (reset_rate)
8510 adapter->vf_data[i].tx_rate = 0;
8511
8512 igb_set_vf_rate_limit(&adapter->hw, i,
8513 adapter->vf_data[i].tx_rate,
8514 actual_link_speed);
8515 }
8516}
8517
8518static int igb_ndo_set_vf_bw(struct net_device *netdev, int vf,
8519 int min_tx_rate, int max_tx_rate)
8520{
8521 struct igb_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
8522 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
8523 int actual_link_speed;
8524
8525 if (hw->mac.type != e1000_82576)
8526 return -EOPNOTSUPP;
8527
8528 if (min_tx_rate)
8529 return -EINVAL;
8530
8531 actual_link_speed = igb_link_mbps(adapter->link_speed);
8532 if ((vf >= adapter->vfs_allocated_count) ||
8533 (!(rd32(E1000_STATUS) & E1000_STATUS_LU)) ||
8534 (max_tx_rate < 0) ||
8535 (max_tx_rate > actual_link_speed))
8536 return -EINVAL;
8537
8538 adapter->vf_rate_link_speed = actual_link_speed;
8539 adapter->vf_data[vf].tx_rate = (u16)max_tx_rate;
8540 igb_set_vf_rate_limit(hw, vf, max_tx_rate, actual_link_speed);
8541
8542 return 0;
8543}
8544
8545static int igb_ndo_set_vf_spoofchk(struct net_device *netdev, int vf,
8546 bool setting)
8547{
8548 struct igb_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
8549 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
8550 u32 reg_val, reg_offset;
8551
8552 if (!adapter->vfs_allocated_count)
8553 return -EOPNOTSUPP;
8554
8555 if (vf >= adapter->vfs_allocated_count)
8556 return -EINVAL;
8557
8558 reg_offset = (hw->mac.type == e1000_82576) ? E1000_DTXSWC : E1000_TXSWC;
8559 reg_val = rd32(reg_offset);
8560 if (setting)
8561 reg_val |= (BIT(vf) |
8562 BIT(vf + E1000_DTXSWC_VLAN_SPOOF_SHIFT));
8563 else
8564 reg_val &= ~(BIT(vf) |
8565 BIT(vf + E1000_DTXSWC_VLAN_SPOOF_SHIFT));
8566 wr32(reg_offset, reg_val);
8567
8568 adapter->vf_data[vf].spoofchk_enabled = setting;
8569 return 0;
8570}
8571
8572static int igb_ndo_get_vf_config(struct net_device *netdev,
8573 int vf, struct ifla_vf_info *ivi)
8574{
8575 struct igb_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
8576 if (vf >= adapter->vfs_allocated_count)
8577 return -EINVAL;
8578 ivi->vf = vf;
8579 memcpy(&ivi->mac, adapter->vf_data[vf].vf_mac_addresses, ETH_ALEN);
8580 ivi->max_tx_rate = adapter->vf_data[vf].tx_rate;
8581 ivi->min_tx_rate = 0;
8582 ivi->vlan = adapter->vf_data[vf].pf_vlan;
8583 ivi->qos = adapter->vf_data[vf].pf_qos;
8584 ivi->spoofchk = adapter->vf_data[vf].spoofchk_enabled;
8585 return 0;
8586}
8587
8588static void igb_vmm_control(struct igb_adapter *adapter)
8589{
8590 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
8591 u32 reg;
8592
8593 switch (hw->mac.type) {
8594 case e1000_82575:
8595 case e1000_i210:
8596 case e1000_i211:
8597 case e1000_i354:
8598 default:
8599 /* replication is not supported for 82575 */
8600 return;
8601 case e1000_82576:
8602 /* notify HW that the MAC is adding vlan tags */
8603 reg = rd32(E1000_DTXCTL);
8604 reg |= E1000_DTXCTL_VLAN_ADDED;
8605 wr32(E1000_DTXCTL, reg);
8606 /* Fall through */
8607 case e1000_82580:
8608 /* enable replication vlan tag stripping */
8609 reg = rd32(E1000_RPLOLR);
8610 reg |= E1000_RPLOLR_STRVLAN;
8611 wr32(E1000_RPLOLR, reg);
8612 /* Fall through */
8613 case e1000_i350:
8614 /* none of the above registers are supported by i350 */
8615 break;
8616 }
8617
8618 if (adapter->vfs_allocated_count) {
8619 igb_vmdq_set_loopback_pf(hw, true);
8620 igb_vmdq_set_replication_pf(hw, true);
8621 igb_vmdq_set_anti_spoofing_pf(hw, true,
8622 adapter->vfs_allocated_count);
8623 } else {
8624 igb_vmdq_set_loopback_pf(hw, false);
8625 igb_vmdq_set_replication_pf(hw, false);
8626 }
8627}
8628
8629static void igb_init_dmac(struct igb_adapter *adapter, u32 pba)
8630{
8631 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
8632 u32 dmac_thr;
8633 u16 hwm;
8634
8635 if (hw->mac.type > e1000_82580) {
8636 if (adapter->flags & IGB_FLAG_DMAC) {
8637 u32 reg;
8638
8639 /* force threshold to 0. */
8640 wr32(E1000_DMCTXTH, 0);
8641
8642 /* DMA Coalescing high water mark needs to be greater
8643 * than the Rx threshold. Set hwm to PBA - max frame
8644 * size in 16B units, capping it at PBA - 6KB.
8645 */
8646 hwm = 64 * (pba - 6);
8647 reg = rd32(E1000_FCRTC);
8648 reg &= ~E1000_FCRTC_RTH_COAL_MASK;
8649 reg |= ((hwm << E1000_FCRTC_RTH_COAL_SHIFT)
8650 & E1000_FCRTC_RTH_COAL_MASK);
8651 wr32(E1000_FCRTC, reg);
8652
8653 /* Set the DMA Coalescing Rx threshold to PBA - 2 * max
8654 * frame size, capping it at PBA - 10KB.
8655 */
8656 dmac_thr = pba - 10;
8657 reg = rd32(E1000_DMACR);
8658 reg &= ~E1000_DMACR_DMACTHR_MASK;
8659 reg |= ((dmac_thr << E1000_DMACR_DMACTHR_SHIFT)
8660 & E1000_DMACR_DMACTHR_MASK);
8661
8662 /* transition to L0x or L1 if available..*/
8663 reg |= (E1000_DMACR_DMAC_EN | E1000_DMACR_DMAC_LX_MASK);
8664
8665 /* watchdog timer= +-1000 usec in 32usec intervals */
8666 reg |= (1000 >> 5);
8667
8668 /* Disable BMC-to-OS Watchdog Enable */
8669 if (hw->mac.type != e1000_i354)
8670 reg &= ~E1000_DMACR_DC_BMC2OSW_EN;
8671
8672 wr32(E1000_DMACR, reg);
8673
8674 /* no lower threshold to disable
8675 * coalescing(smart fifb)-UTRESH=0
8676 */
8677 wr32(E1000_DMCRTRH, 0);
8678
8679 reg = (IGB_DMCTLX_DCFLUSH_DIS | 0x4);
8680
8681 wr32(E1000_DMCTLX, reg);
8682
8683 /* free space in tx packet buffer to wake from
8684 * DMA coal
8685 */
8686 wr32(E1000_DMCTXTH, (IGB_MIN_TXPBSIZE -
8687 (IGB_TX_BUF_4096 + adapter->max_frame_size)) >> 6);
8688
8689 /* make low power state decision controlled
8690 * by DMA coal
8691 */
8692 reg = rd32(E1000_PCIEMISC);
8693 reg &= ~E1000_PCIEMISC_LX_DECISION;
8694 wr32(E1000_PCIEMISC, reg);
8695 } /* endif adapter->dmac is not disabled */
8696 } else if (hw->mac.type == e1000_82580) {
8697 u32 reg = rd32(E1000_PCIEMISC);
8698
8699 wr32(E1000_PCIEMISC, reg & ~E1000_PCIEMISC_LX_DECISION);
8700 wr32(E1000_DMACR, 0);
8701 }
8702}
8703
8704/**
8705 * igb_read_i2c_byte - Reads 8 bit word over I2C
8706 * @hw: pointer to hardware structure
8707 * @byte_offset: byte offset to read
8708 * @dev_addr: device address
8709 * @data: value read
8710 *
8711 * Performs byte read operation over I2C interface at
8712 * a specified device address.
8713 **/
8714s32 igb_read_i2c_byte(struct e1000_hw *hw, u8 byte_offset,
8715 u8 dev_addr, u8 *data)
8716{
8717 struct igb_adapter *adapter = container_of(hw, struct igb_adapter, hw);
8718 struct i2c_client *this_client = adapter->i2c_client;
8719 s32 status;
8720 u16 swfw_mask = 0;
8721
8722 if (!this_client)
8723 return E1000_ERR_I2C;
8724
8725 swfw_mask = E1000_SWFW_PHY0_SM;
8726
8727 if (hw->mac.ops.acquire_swfw_sync(hw, swfw_mask))
8728 return E1000_ERR_SWFW_SYNC;
8729
8730 status = i2c_smbus_read_byte_data(this_client, byte_offset);
8731 hw->mac.ops.release_swfw_sync(hw, swfw_mask);
8732
8733 if (status < 0)
8734 return E1000_ERR_I2C;
8735 else {
8736 *data = status;
8737 return 0;
8738 }
8739}
8740
8741/**
8742 * igb_write_i2c_byte - Writes 8 bit word over I2C
8743 * @hw: pointer to hardware structure
8744 * @byte_offset: byte offset to write
8745 * @dev_addr: device address
8746 * @data: value to write
8747 *
8748 * Performs byte write operation over I2C interface at
8749 * a specified device address.
8750 **/
8751s32 igb_write_i2c_byte(struct e1000_hw *hw, u8 byte_offset,
8752 u8 dev_addr, u8 data)
8753{
8754 struct igb_adapter *adapter = container_of(hw, struct igb_adapter, hw);
8755 struct i2c_client *this_client = adapter->i2c_client;
8756 s32 status;
8757 u16 swfw_mask = E1000_SWFW_PHY0_SM;
8758
8759 if (!this_client)
8760 return E1000_ERR_I2C;
8761
8762 if (hw->mac.ops.acquire_swfw_sync(hw, swfw_mask))
8763 return E1000_ERR_SWFW_SYNC;
8764 status = i2c_smbus_write_byte_data(this_client, byte_offset, data);
8765 hw->mac.ops.release_swfw_sync(hw, swfw_mask);
8766
8767 if (status)
8768 return E1000_ERR_I2C;
8769 else
8770 return 0;
8771
8772}
8773
8774int igb_reinit_queues(struct igb_adapter *adapter)
8775{
8776 struct net_device *netdev = adapter->netdev;
8777 struct pci_dev *pdev = adapter->pdev;
8778 int err = 0;
8779
8780 if (netif_running(netdev))
8781 igb_close(netdev);
8782
8783 igb_reset_interrupt_capability(adapter);
8784
8785 if (igb_init_interrupt_scheme(adapter, true)) {
8786 dev_err(&pdev->dev, "Unable to allocate memory for queues\n");
8787 return -ENOMEM;
8788 }
8789
8790 if (netif_running(netdev))
8791 err = igb_open(netdev);
8792
8793 return err;
8794}
8795
8796static void igb_nfc_filter_exit(struct igb_adapter *adapter)
8797{
8798 struct igb_nfc_filter *rule;
8799
8800 spin_lock(&adapter->nfc_lock);
8801
8802 hlist_for_each_entry(rule, &adapter->nfc_filter_list, nfc_node)
8803 igb_erase_filter(adapter, rule);
8804
8805 spin_unlock(&adapter->nfc_lock);
8806}
8807
8808static void igb_nfc_filter_restore(struct igb_adapter *adapter)
8809{
8810 struct igb_nfc_filter *rule;
8811
8812 spin_lock(&adapter->nfc_lock);
8813
8814 hlist_for_each_entry(rule, &adapter->nfc_filter_list, nfc_node)
8815 igb_add_filter(adapter, rule);
8816
8817 spin_unlock(&adapter->nfc_lock);
8818}
